@startuml HLD-Overview

title High-Level Design — Topic Map

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam packageBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

package "High-Level Design Topics" {

    package "Traffic Management" {
        [Load Balancing]       #DDEEFF
        [API Gateway]          #DDEEFF
        [Rate Limiting]        #DDEEFF
    }

    package "Data Layer" {
        [Caching]              #D5E8D4
        [Database Sharding]    #D5E8D4
        [Consistent Hashing]   #D5E8D4
    }

    package "Async & Messaging" {
        [Message Queue]        #FFF2CC
    }

    package "Reliability" {
        [Circuit Breaker]      #F8CECC
        [Idempotency]          #F8CECC
    }
}

note right of [Load Balancing]
  Distributes incoming traffic across
  multiple servers (Round Robin, Least
  Connections, IP Hash).
end note

note right of [Caching]
  Reduces DB load with in-memory stores
  (Redis, Memcached). Strategies:
  Cache-Aside, Write-Through, Write-Back.
end note

note right of [Rate Limiting]
  Controls request rate per client.
  Algorithms: Token Bucket, Leaky Bucket,
  Fixed/Sliding Window Counter.
end note

note right of [Message Queue]
  Decouples producers & consumers.
  Tools: Kafka, RabbitMQ, SQS.
  Patterns: Pub/Sub, Point-to-Point.
end note

note right of [Database Sharding]
  Horizontally partitions data across
  multiple DB nodes. Types: Range,
  Hash, Directory sharding.
end note

note right of [API Gateway]
  Single entry point: auth, routing,
  rate-limiting, SSL termination,
  request aggregation.
end note

note right of [Circuit Breaker]
  Prevents cascading failures.
  States: CLOSED → OPEN → HALF-OPEN.
end note

note right of [Consistent Hashing]
  Minimises key remapping when nodes
  are added/removed. Used in CDN,
  distributed caches.
end note

note right of [Idempotency]
  Guarantees duplicate requests produce
  the same result (safe retries).
  Key stored with TTL.
end note

@enduml

